[32m│[0m ### **Critical Security Findings**                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m #### **1. 2FA Bypass Vulnerability (CRITICAL)**                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Location:** `/admin/2fa` page JavaScript                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Finding:** The 2FA form captures user OTP input but completely ignores it, [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m sending a hardcoded value instead:                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```javascript                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m $("form").submit(function(e) {                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m     e.preventDefault();                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m     var otp = $("#otp").val();  // User input captured but NOT used          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m     $.ajax({                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m         url: "/admin/2fa",                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m         type: "POST",                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m         data: {                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m             code: 1234,  // HARDCODED VALUE - always sends 1234              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m         },                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m         success: function(data) {                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m             if (data.success == true) {                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                 window.location.href = '/admin/dashboard';                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m             }                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m         }                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m     });                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m });                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Impact:** The 2FA mechanism can be bypassed by sending `code=1234` to the  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `/admin/2fa` endpoint.                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Testing performed:**                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Direct POST to `/admin/2fa` with `code=1234` returns `{"success": true}`   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - However, this alone doesn't create a valid session                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Needs to be chained with a successful login to work as a complete bypass   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m #### **2. Werkzeug Debug Console Exposed (CRITICAL)**                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Location:** `/console` and `/logout`                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
